# OSMO Mermaid Architecture Docs

This folder contains architecture diagrams and a codebase snapshot for the OSMO trading stack.

## Repositories

| Layer | Repo | Local Folder |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Frontend | https://github.com/TradeWithOsmo/osmo-web | `v1-web` |
| Backend | https://github.com/TradeWithOsmo/osmo-backend | `backend` |
| Smart Contracts | https://github.com/TradeWithOsmo/osmo-contracts | `contracts` |

## Codebase Snapshot

### 1) Frontend (`v1-web`)
- Stack: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite.
- Main pages: Trade, Portfolio, Arena, Leaderboard, Usage, Faucet.
- Key modules:
  - `src/charting/` (TradingView chart integration, command handlers, datafeeds)
  - `src/api/` (onchain, orders, portfolio, leaderboard, agent, usage services)
  - `src/components/Autos/` (AI chat interface and workspace)
  - `src/contracts/abis/` (ABI bindings for on-chain modules)
- Typical run:
  - `npm run dev`
  - `npm run build`

### 2) Backend (`backend`)
- Stack: Python services with agent runtime + websocket API service.
- Main services:
  - `backend/websocket/` (API routers, market data, ledger, leaderboard, chat, arena services)
  - `backend/agent/` (tool orchestration, reasoning runtime, TradingView tools, trade/data tools)
- Includes:
  - connector pipelines (Hyperliquid/Ostium),
  - candle/history services,
  - AI tool routing and runtime safety gates.

### 3) Smart Contracts (`contracts`)
- Stack: Foundry-based Solidity project.
- Main modules:
  - core hub: `src/core/OsmoHub.sol`
  - trading: vault, order router, position manager, adapters
  - risk + security modules
  - fees + AI credit vault
  - oracle + symbol registry
  - arena modules (`ArenaChooseSide`, `ArenaPoints`, `ArenaSecurity`)
- Config highlights:
  - `foundry.toml` uses `src/`, `out/`, `lib/`
  - CI profile for fuzz and invariant testing.

## Diagram Index

- `AI-Architecture.mmd`
  - Agent orchestration flow: prompt -> reasoning/action -> tools -> model router -> output.
